ied Sentinel torso stand\n|\n|Uncanny X-Men (1963) #129\n|-\n|[[Mr. Fantastic]]\n|interchangeable arms and [[Fantasticar]] stand\n|\n|Fantastic Four (1961) #489\n|-\n|[[Nick Fury]]\n|gun and flaming jetpack stand\n|\n|Nick Fury, Agent of S.H.I.E.L.D. (1968) #1\n|-\n|[[Red Skull]]\n|peak cap, gun and stand\n|\n|Captain America (1968) #16\n|-\n|[[Sabretooth (comics)|Sabretooth]]\n|disembodied Sentinel leg stand\n|\n|X-Men (1991) #5\n|-\n|[[Silver Surfer]] and [[Howard the Duck]]\n|Surfboard\n|\n|Silver Surfer (1968) #11\n|-\n\n|rowspan=9|6\n|rowspan=9|September 2004\n|rowspan=2|[[Cable (comics)|Cable]]\n|rowspan=2|Guns and interchangeable gun stand\n|Blue\n|rowspan=2|Cable (1993) #73\n|-\n|brown variant\n|-\n|[[Deadpool (comics)|Deadpool]] and [[Doop (comics)|Doop]]\n|guns, swords, flight stand (for Doop)\n|\n|Deadpool (1994) #4\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[Jean Grey]]\n|rowspan=2|stand\n|Phoenix\n|rowspan=2|Uncanny X-Men (1963) #101\n|-\n|Dark Phoenix variant\n|-\n|[[Juggernaut (comics)|Juggernaut]]\n|destroyed Xavier Institute stand\n|\n|Uncanny X-Men (1963) #13\n|-\n|[[Punisher]]\n|bazooka, guns and stand\n|[[The Punisher (2004 film)]] version\n|The Amazing Spider-Man (1963) #129\n|-\n|rowspan=2|Wolverine\n|rowspan=2|[[Ogun (comics)|Ogun]] base with Muramasa blade\n|Brown\n|rowspan=2|Uncanny X-Men (1963) #213\n|-\n|unmasked variant (Series 3 re-release)\n|-\n|rowspan=10|7\n|rowspan=10|December 2004\n|[[Apocalypse (comics)|Apocalypse]]\n|Egyptian stand\n|\n|X-Factor (1986) #25\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[Ghost Rider (Johnny Blaze)]]\n|Motorcycle\n|\n|rowspan=2|\n|-\n|Flaming motorcycle\n|phasing variant\n|-\n|[[Hank Pym|Goliath (Pym)]], [[Ant-Man (Scott Lang)|Ant-Man (Lang)]], and [[Wasp (comics)|Wasp]]\n|\n|Series 4 rerelease\n|The Avengers (1963) #28\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[Hawkeye (Clint Barton)|Hawkeye]]\n|rowspan=2|arrows, bow, quiver and Sky-Cycle on rock stand\n|classic\n|rowspan=2|Avengers (1963) #223\n|-\n|Knuckle guard bow variant\n|-\n|Iron Man\n|Rocket launcher stand\n|[[Iron Man 