t/green pants\n|rowspan=2|Uncanny X-Men (1963) #141\n|-\n|''Younger'' Logan, white T-shirt/blue pants and cowboy hat variant\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[Wonder Man]] and [[Hank Pym|Yellowjacket]]\n|rowspan=2|red jet scooter\n|small Yellowjacket attaches to shoulder\n|rowspan=2|Avengers (1998) #51\n|-\n|translucent purple ionic, small Yellowjacket attaches to shoulder\n|}\n\n===Build-A-Figure===\nIn 2005, Toy Biz introduced the \"Build-A-Figure\" (referred to as a \"BAF\" in the collector community) starting with series 9. Each figure in the series was packaged with a piece of a larger figure. A consumer who bought each figure in the assortment would then have all the complete components to assemble a character unavailable in individual packaging.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!width=5%|'''Build-A-Figure'''\n!width=5%|'''Release'''\n!width=15%|'''Figure'''\n!width=25%|'''Accessories'''\n!width=25%|'''Description'''\n!width=15%|'''Comic'''\n!width=10%|'''Build-A-Figure Piece'''\n|-\n|rowspan=9|[[Galactus]]\n|rowspan=9|February 2005\n|rowspan=2|[[Bullseye (comics)|Bullseye]]\n|rowspan=2|stand\n|white\n|rowspan=2|Daredevil (1964) #132\n|rowspan=2|leg, left\n|-\n|gritting teeth/gray variant\n|-\n|[[Deathlok]]\n|\n|\n|Deathlok (1990) #3\n|Upper torso\n|-\n|rowspan=2|Hulk\n|rowspan=2|\n|Grey (first appearance)/closed mouth version\n|rowspan=2|Incredible Hulk (1968) #1\n|rowspan=2|arm, left\n|-\n|Green variant\n|-\n|[[Nightcrawler (comics)|Nightcrawler]]\n|\n|\n|Poster book\n|Lower torso\n|-\n|[[Doctor Strange]]\n|\n|\n|4 selections from ''Strange Tales''\n|arm, right\n|-\n|[[War Machine]]\n|Guns, rocket launcher and blast effects\n|[[Marvel MAX|U.S. War Machine]] version\n|Iron Man (1968) #281\n|leg, right\n|-\n|[[Professor X]]\n|Helmet and wheelchair\n|\n|Uncanny X-Men (1963) #117\n|Head\n|-\n|rowspan=9|[[Sentinels (comics)|Sentinel]]\n|rowspan=9|September 2005\n|rowspan=2|[[Warren Worthington III|Angel]]\n|rowspan=2|clear flight stand\n|Red Costume\n|rowspan=2|Uncanny X-Men (1963) #5