in (comics)|Mandarin]]\n|Iron Man\n|rowspan=4|\n|Modular Armor\n|rowspan=4|Iron Man (1968) #311\n|-\n|Mandarin\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[War Machine]] versus Mandarin (Variant)\n|War Machine\n|\n|-\n|Mandarin\n|Red costume\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[Punisher]] versus [[Jigsaw (Marvel Comics)|Jigsaw]]\n|Punisher\n|rowspan=4|rifles, base and background\n|Classic\n|rowspan=4|Punisher (1987) #36\n|-\n|Jigsaw\n|Punisher costume\n|-\n|rowspan=2|Punisher versus Jigsaw (Variant)\n|Punisher\n|Modern\n|-\n|Jigsaw\n|Business suit\n|}\n\n==Hasbro==\nAfter Hasbro gained the rights to produce Marvel toys, the company continued with the theme of Build-A-Figure pieces. Also, Hasbro's new molds mostly eliminated finger joints, a mainstay of the Toy Biz era, and the comic book pack-ins.\n*All the figures in the Terrax and Arnim Zola waves were labelled with a \"The Return of Marvel Legends\" sticker.\n*The Hit-Monkey, Rocket Raccoon, and Jubilee waves used the \"Mini\" Build-A-Figure concept.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!width=10%|'''Build-A-Figure'''\n!width=5%|'''Release'''\n!width=15%|'''Figure'''\n!width=30%|'''Accessories'''\n!width=30%|'''Description'''\n!width=20%|'''Build-A-Figure Piece'''\n|-\n|rowspan=6|[[Annihilus]]\n|rowspan=6|2007\n|[[Banshee (comics)|Banshee]]\n|\n|\n|Right wing\n|-\n|[[Beast (Marvel Comics)|Beast]]\n|\n|[[X-Men: The Last Stand]] version\n|Left arm and leg\n|-\n|[[Emma Frost]]\n|\n|\n|Right arm and leg\n|-\n|[[Hercules (Marvel Comics)|Hercules]]\n|mace\n|\n|Left wing\n|-\n|Gladiator Hulk\n|shield and removable helmet\n|Originally shipped with an erroneous silver left arm, but this was later updated to the correct green one.<br />Retool of the [[Hulk Classics]] [[Horsemen of Apocalypse|War Hulk]] figure from ToyBiz with a new head and accessories.\n|Head\n|-\n|[[Ultimate Iron Man (character)|Ultimate Iron Man]]\n|\n|Packaged with helmet on or off\n|Torso\n|-\n|rowspan=12|[[Blob (comics)|Blob]]\n|rowspan=12|2007\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[Jean Grey]]\n|\n|[[X-Men: The Last Stand