hield and alternate right hand with shield toss effect piece\n|Classic<br />Redeco of Onslaught wave with a new scale mail pattern\n|-\n|Iron Man\n|2 blast effect pieces\n|Neo-Classic Armor<br />Retool of Epic Heroes\n|-\n|[[Wolverine (character)|Wolverine]]\n|Alternate unmasked head and removed mask\n|80s brown costume<br />Repaint of Juggernaut wave with a new head and accessories\n|-\n|[[Spider-Man]]\n|Pizza slice and alternate head with exposed mouth\n|Repaint of Hobgoblin wave\n|-\n|[[Black Widow (Natalia Romanova)]]\n|Twin pistols\n|Classic\n|-\n|[[Punisher]]\n|Bazooka and alternate head\n|90s<br />Repaint of the Walgreens exclusive\n|-\n|rowspan=6|2\n|[[Wasp (comics)|Wasp]]\n|Miniature Ant-Man\n|[[George Perez]] version\n|-\n|[[Hank Pym|Ant-Man (Hank Pym)]]\n|Miniature Wasp\n|Classic version\n|-\n|[[Black Panther (Marvel Comics)|Black Panther]]\n|Alternate hands and two kinetic blast effect pieces\n|Modern version<br />Repaint of the All-New, All-Different Black Panther\n|-\n|[[Hawkeye (Clint Barton)|Hawkeye]]\n|Bow and quiver\n|Classic version<br />Retool of the Allfather wave Hawkeye with new arms\n|-\n|[[Vision (Marvel Comics)|Vision]]\n|Ultron head\n|Classic version\n|-\n|[[Scarlet Spider (Ben Reilly)]]\n|Alternate hands and unmasked head\n|Repaint of the Rhino series Scarlet Spider with new accessories\n|-\n|rowspan=6|X-Men\n|[[Wolverine (character)|Wolverine]]\n|Muramasa blade\n|[[Madripoor]] outfit version\n|-\n|[[Storm (Marvel Comics)|Storm]]\n|Two lightning effect pieces\n|Jim Lee version\n|-\n|[[Cyclops (Marvel Comics)|Cyclops]]\n|Alternate head and optic blast effect piece\n|[[X-Factor (comics)|X-Factor]] version<br />Redeco of the Toys R Us 2-pack\n|-\n|[[Dazzler (Marvel Comics)|Dazzler]]\n|Energy effect\n|80s version\n|-\n|[[Silver Samurai]]\n|Katana and [[wakizashi]]\n|\n|-\n|[[Iceman (Marvel Comics)|Iceman]]\n|Ice display base\n|Jim Lee version<br />Retool of the Juggernaut wave Iceman with a new headsculpt\n|-\n|rowspan=3|Fan Channel exclusives\n|[[Storm (Marvel Comics)|Storm]]\n|2 lightning effect pieces\n|Black costume version<br>Repaint of the Jim Lee Storm figure\n|-\n|[[Beast (Marvel Comics)|Beast]]\n|Book, reading glasses and alternate head and hands\n|Gray version<br>Repaint of the Caliban wave Beast figure with a new head and accessories \n|-\n|[[Mysterio (comics)|Mysterio]]\n|2 smoke effect pieces\n|Repaint of the Lizard wave Mysterio\n|}\n\n===Deluxe figures===\nFigures at a higher price point that are larger or come with additional accessories.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!width=20%| Figure\n!width=6%| Year\n!width=54%| Accessories\n!width=20%| Description\n|-\n|[[Archangel (comics)|Archangel]]\n|2018\n|Attachable wings, 3 alternate heads and an alternate claw hand for the 2018 Apocalypse BAF\n|Jim Lee version<br />Repaint of the SDDC exclusive X-Force box set Archangel with new accessories<br>Gamestop and Entertainment Earth exclusive\n|-\n|[[Scott Lang|Giant-Man]]\n|2019\n|\n|[[Captain America: Civil War]] version<br>Rerelease of the 2016 BAF\n|-\n|[[Black Widow (Natalia Romanova)|Black Widow (Natasha Romanoff)]]\n|2020\n|Adjustable display stand, 4 alternate hands, twin pistols, 2 ice axes, 2 electric shock effect pieces and 7 explosion effect pieces\n|[[Black Widow (2020 film)]] winter camo version\n|}\n\n===Vehicles===\nA series of figures that come packaged with vehicles, similar to the ToyBiz Legendary Riders wave.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!width=20%| Figure\n!width=6%| Year\n!width=54%| Accessories\n!width=20%| Description\n|-\n|[[Black Widow (Natalia Romanova)]]\n|rowspan=3|2018\n|Motorcycle and alternate head\n|\n|-\n|[[Ghost Rider (Johnny Blaze)]]\n|Hell Cycle and flaming chain\n|Repaint of the Rhino series\n|-\n|[[Wolverine (character)|Logan]]\n|Motorcycle, alternate \"Patch\" head and hands\n|Casual clothes\n|-\n|[[Professor X]]\n|rowspan=3|2019\n|Hover chair, [[Cerebro]] helmet, hover effect and alternate [[Shadow King]] head for the Kingpin BAF\n|Jim Lee version\n|-\n|[