n|Claw gauntlets, and latex glove hands\n|[[Iron Fist (TV series)]] version<br />Exclusive\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=2|Avengers: Infinity War\n|rowspan=2|2019\n|[[Corvus Glaive]]\n|Glaive\n|[[Avengers: Infinity War]] version<br />Exclusive\n|\n|-\n|[[Loki (Marvel Comics)|Loki]]\n|[[Cosmic Cube|Tesseract]]\n|[[Avengers: Infinity War]] version<br />Redeco of the Gladiator Hulk wave Loki\n|\n|}\n\n==Showdown==\n[[Marvel Legends Showdown]] is a collectible tabletop game in which the primary component is {{convert|4|in|mm|adj=on}} action figures and cards. It was a collaboration between [[Upper Deck Entertainment]] and Toy Biz. Originally known as Marvel Superhero Showdown.\n\n==Unleashed (2008)==\nFigures are {{convert|8|in|mm|adj=on}}. The figures were produced by Hasbro and feature multiple points of articulation.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:40%;\"\n|-\n!width=5%|'''Wave'''\n!width=15%|'''Figure'''\n!width=20%|'''Description'''\n|-\n|rowspan=2|1\n|Spider-Man\n|\n|-\n|Green Goblin\n|Marvel Knights costume\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2\n|Spider-Man\n|Symbiote costume\n|-\n|Doctor Octopus\n|\n|-\n|3\n|Iron Man\n|Anti-radiation armor\n|}\n\n==Icons==\nThe series is {{convert|12|in|mm|adj=on}}.\n\n===Toy Biz===\nFigures come with an \"Evolution of an Icon\" comic sized book including a history and statistics of the character as well as artwork.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!width=5%|'''Series'''\n!width=5%|'''Release'''\n!width=15%|'''Figure'''\n!width=25%|'''Accessories'''\n!width=45%|'''Description'''\n|-\n|rowspan=6|1\n|rowspan=14|2006\n|rowspan=2|Captain America\n|rowspan=2|Shield\n|Masked\n|-\n|Unmasked\n|-\n|rowspan=2|Iron Man\n|rowspan=2|2 blast effects, removable mask\n|Upscaled version of Armor Model 24<ref>http://marvel.wikia.com/wiki/Iron_Man_Armor_Model_24</ref>\n|-\n|Gold variant\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[Wolverine (character)|Wolverine]]\n|rowspan=2|\n|Masked\n|-\n|Unmasked\n|-\n|rowspan=4|2\n|rowspan=2|Hulk\n|rowspan=2|\n|Green\n|-\n|Grey\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[Venom (Marvel Comics character)|Venom]]\n|rowspan=2|\n|Upscaled version of the [[Spider-Man Classics]] Symbiote Blast figure\n|-\n|Eddie Brock head\n|-\n|rowspan=4|3\n|rowspan=2|[[Beast (comics)|Beast]]\n|\n|Gray fur\n|-\n|lab coat and glasses\n|Blue fur\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[Spider-Man]]\n|rowspan=2|\n|Regular\n|-\n|Unmasked\n|}\n\n===Hasbro===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!width=5%|'''Wave'''\n!width=5%|'''Release'''\n!width=15%|'''Figure'''\n!width=35%|'''Accessories'''\n!width=35%|'''Description'''\n|-\n|rowspan=2|1\n|rowspan=9|2007\n|Thor\n|Mjolnir\n|cloth cape\n|-\n|Wolverine\n|\n|Toy Biz series 1 repaint, brown costume\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2\n|[[Doctor Doom]]\n|Pistol\n|cloth cape\n|-\n|[[Punisher]]\n|[[M16 rifle|M-16]], knife, pistol\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=3|3\n|rowspan=2|[[Human Torch]]\n|rowspan=2|\n|Regular\n|-\n|Flame-off Johnny Storm\n|-\n|[[Silver Surfer]]\n|surfboard\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=2|4\n|[[Cyclops (Marvel Comics)|Cyclops]]\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[Magneto (Marvel Comics)|Magneto]]\n|Helmet\n|cloth cape\n|-\n|rowspan=3|5\n|rowspan=7|2009\n|rowspan=2|Daredevil\n|rowspan=2|batons\n|red\n|-\n|yellow & brown\n|-\n|Nightcrawler\n|\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=4|6\n|-\n|Colossus\n|\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=2|Jean Grey\n|rowspan=2|\n|Phoenix\n|-\n|Dark Phoenix \n|}\n\n=====12-Inch=====\nIn 2016 12-inch Legends returned effectively reviving the concept of the Icons line in all but name. The figures are more expensive and are therefore aimed at a more adult collector market.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!width=5%|'''Release'''\n!width=15%|'''Figure'''\n!width=57%|'''Accessories'''\n!width=23%|'''Description'''\n|-\n|rowspan=3|2016\n|Iron Man\n|Alternate unmasked head, interchangeable hands and blast effects.\n|Model 37 Bleeding Edge armor<ref>http://marvel.wikia.com/wiki/Iron_Man_Armor_Model_37</ref>\n|-\n|Captain America\n|Shield, alternate unmasked head and helmet and interchangeable hands\n|[[Marvel NOW!]] version\n|-\n|Spider-Man\n|2 alternate heads and four interchangeable hands\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=5|2017\n|Deadpool and [[Headpool]]\n|2 alternate heads, 2 katanas, 2 guns, four alternate hands, 2 knives, a [[chimichanga]] and flight stand for Headpool\n|\n|-\n|Spider-Man\n|Alternate unmasked head and 4 interchangeable hands\n|Symbiote (Target exclusive)\n|-\n|Thor\n|Alternate helmeted head, 2interchangeable hands and 2 Mjolnirs\n|\n|-\n|Hulk\n|Alternate head and 2 interchangeable hands\n|\n|-\n|Daredevil\n|Alternate unmasked head and mask, six interchangeable hands and 2 batons\n|San Diego Comic Convention exclusive\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2018\n|Black Panther\n|Alternate unmasked head, Vibranium spear and 2 sets of interchangeable hands\n|[[Black Panther (film)]] version\n|-\n|Wolverine\n|2 alternate heads and a mask, 2 interchangeable hands and 2 interchangeable shoulder pads\n|\n|}\n\n==Prop Replicas==\nIn 2016, Hasbro announced a line of high end role play accessories. After the release of the first two items, a poll was held to determine future entries in the line.<ref>http://comicsalliance.com/hasbro-marvel-legends-role-play-vote/</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!width=10%|'''Release'''\n!width=30%|'''Item'''\n!width=60%|'''Description'''\n|-\n|\n|[[Iron Man]]'s helmet\n|removable faceplate<br />light-up eyes<br />sound effects\n|-\n|\n|[[Captain America's shield]]\n|adjustable straps\n|-\n|\n|[[Mjolnir (Marvel Comics)|Mjolnir]]\n|voice-activated light-up Odin symbol<br />sound effects<br />display stand\n|-\n|\n|[[Star-Lord]]'s helmet\n|[[Bluetooth]] speakers<br />light-up eyes\n|-\n|\n|[[Black Panther (comics)|Black Panther]]'s mask\n|light-up [[Vibranium]] effect<br />retractable lenses\n|-\n|\n|[[Infinity Gauntlet (weapon)|Infinity Gauntlet]]\n|light-up [[Infinity Stones]], sound effects, articulated fingers\n|-\n|\n|[[Ant-Man]]'s helmet\n|LEDs\n|-\n|\n|[[Infinity Gauntlet (weapon)|Stark Power Gauntlet]]\n|[[Avengers: Endgame]] version<br />light-up Infinity Stones\n|-\n|\n|[[War Machine]]'s helmet\n|[[Punisher (comics)|Punisher]] skull logo version<br />removable faceplate<br />light-up eyes<br />sound effects\n|}\n\n==Announced==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:5%;\"|'''Release'''\n! style=\"width:8%;\"|'''Wave'''\n! style=\"width:11%;\"|'''Figure'''\n! style=\"width:28%;\"|'''Accessories'''\n! style=\"width:40%;\"|'''Description'''\n! style=\"width:13%;\"|'''Build-A-Figure Piece'''\n|-\n|rowspan=7|2020\n|rowspan=7|[[Sugar Man]]\n|[[Alternative versions of Wolverine#Age of Apocalypse|Weapon X]] \n|Alternate left arm stub\n|rowspan=7|[[Age of Apocalypse]] version\n|Left leg\n|-\n|[[X-Man]]\n|\n|Top arms\n|-\n|[[Morph (Marvel Comics)|Morph]]\n|\n|Right leg\n|-\n|[[Wild Child (comics)|Wild Child]]\n|Chain\n|Torso\n|-\n|[[Sunfire (comics)|Sunfire]]\n|\n|Bottom arms\n|-\n|[[Dark Beast]]\n|Alternate hands\n|Hammer\n|-\n|[[Jean Grey]]\n|\n|Head\n|-\n\n|rowspan=5|2020\n|rowspan=5|[[Strong Guy]]\n|[[Deadpool]]\n|Twin katanas and rifle\n|Blue and yellow X-Men uniform version<br>Repaint of the Sasquatch wave Deadpool with different accessories\n|\n|-\n|[[Sunspot (comics)|Sunspot]]\n|2 energy effect pieces\n|rowspan=2|Rob Liefeld version\n|\n|-\n|[[Warpath (comics)|Warpath]]\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[Black Tom Cassidy]]\n|Shillelagh\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[Maverick (Marvel Comics)|Maverick]]\n|Gun\n|\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=7|2020\n|rowspan=7|[[Abomination (comics)|Abomination]] (Gamerverse)\n|[[Iron Man]]\n|2 blast effect pieces\n|rowspan=2|[[Avengers (2020 video game)]] version\n|Right leg\n|-\n|[[Captain America]]\n|Shield\n|\n|-\n|[[Ms. Marvel (Kamala Khan)]]\n|Alternate enlarged hands\n|[[Avengers (2020 video game)]] version<br>Redeco and retool of the Sandman wave Ms. Marvel figure with new boots\n|Torso\n|-\n|[[Captain Marvel (Mar-Vell)]]\n|\n|\n|Left arm\n|-\n|[[The Leader (comics)|The Leader]]\n|\n|\n|Left leg\n|-\n|[[Abner Jenkins|Mach-1]]\n|\n|\n|Head\n|-\n|[[Rage (Marvel Comics)|Rage]]\n|\n|\n|Right arm\n|-\n|rowspan=7|2020\n|rowspan=7|[[Crimson Dynamo]]\n|[[