ptember 2005\n|Iron Man\n|glider\n|[[Iron Man armors#Hulkbuster Armor, Mk I|Hulkbuster armor]]\n|Iron Man (1968) #305\n|-\n|[[Scarlet Witch]]\n|scooter\n|\n|Avengers (1964) #187\n|-\n|[[Taskmaster (comics)|Taskmaster]]\n|Sky-Cycle, gun, sword and cane\n|same as packaged with Hawkeye\n|Avengers (1963) #196\n|-\n|Thing\n|jet scooter\n|first appearance version\n|Fantastic Four (1961) #1\n|-\n|[[Ultron]]\n|glider\n|\n|Avengers (1998) #22\n|-\n|[[Vengeance (comics)|Vengeance]]\n|motorcycle\n|\n|Ghost Rider (1990) #39\n|-\n|rowspan=2|Wolverine\n|rowspan=2|motorcycle\n|Days of Future Past Logan, black T-shirt/green pants\n|rowspan=2|Uncanny X-Men (1963) #141\n|-\n|''Younger'' Logan, white T-shirt/blue pants and cowboy hat variant\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[Wonder Man]] and [[Hank Pym|Yellowjacket]]\n|rowspan=2|red jet scooter\n|small Yellowjacket attaches to shoulder\n|rowspan=2|Avengers (1998) #51\n|-\n|translucent purple ionic, small Yellowjacket attaches to shoulder\n|}\n\n===Build-A-Figure===\nIn 2005, Toy Biz introduced the \"Build-A-Figure\" (referred to as a \"BAF\" in the collector community) starting with series 9. Each figure in the series was packaged with a piece of a larger figure. A consumer who bought each figure in the assortment would then have all the complete components to assemble a character unavailable in individual packaging.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!width=5%|'''Build-A-Figure'''\n!width=5%|'''Release'''\n!width=15%|'''Figure'''\n!width=25%|'''Accessories'''\n!width=25%|'''Description'''\n!width=15%|'''Comic'''\n!width=10%|'''Build-A-Figure Piece'''\n|-\n|rowspan=9|[[Galactus]]\n|rowspan=9|February 2005\n|rowspan=2|[[Bullseye (comics)|Bullseye]]\n|rowspan=2|stand\n|white\n|rowspan=2|Daredevil (1964) #132\n|rowspan=2|leg, left\n|-\n|gritting teeth/gray variant\n|-\n|[[Deathlok]]\n|\n|\n|Deathlok (1990) #3\n|Upper torso\n|-\n|rowspan=2|Hulk\n|rowspan=2|\n|Grey (first appearance)/closed mouth version\n|rowspan=2|Incredible Hulk (1968) #1\n|rowspan=2|arm, left\n|-\n|Green variant\n|-\n|[[Nightcrawler (comics)|Nightcrawler]]\n|\n|\n|Poster book\n|Lower torso\n|-\n|[[Doctor Strange]]\n|\n|\n|4 selections from ''Strange Tales''\n|arm, right\n|-\n|[[War Machine]]\n|Guns, rocket launcher and blast effects\n|[[Marvel MAX|U.S. War Machine]] version\n|Iron Man (1968) #281\n|leg, right\n|-\n|[[Professor X]]\n|Helmet and wheelchair\n|\n|Uncanny X-Men (1963) #117\n|Head\n|-\n|rowspan=9|[[Sentinels (comics)|Sentinel]]\n|rowspan=9|September 2005\n|rowspan=2|[[Warren Worthington III|Angel]]\n|rowspan=2|clear flight stand\n|Red Costume\n|rowspan=2|Uncanny X-Men (1963) #5\n|rowspan=2|leg, left\n|-\n|light blue costume variant\n|-\n|[[Black Panther (comics)|Black Panther]]\n|clear flight stand\n|[[Marvel Knights]] version\n|Avengers (1963) #87\n|arm, right\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[Cyclops (Marvel Comics)|Cyclops]]\n|rowspan=2|clear flight stand\n|Blue and yellow costume\n|rowspan=2|Uncanny X-Men (1963) #201\n|rowspan=2|arm, left\n|-\n|[[X-Factor (comics)|X-Factor]] costume variant\n|-\n|[[Mister Sinister]]\n|clear flight stand\n|\n|Uncanny X-Men (1963) #243\n|leg, right\n|-\n|[[Mystique (comics)|Mystique]]\n|clear flight stand\n|\n|Poster Book\n|rowspan=2|lower torso\n|-\n|[[Omega Red]]\n|2 tentacles\n|\n|X-Men (1991) #7\n|-\n|[[Spider-Man]]\n|clear flight stand\n|first appearance [[Steve Ditko]] version\n|Origin story from Amazing Fantasy (1963) #15 and Amazing Spider-Man (1963) #8\n|Head and upper torso\n|-\n|rowspan=11|[[Apocalypse (comics)|Apocalypse]]\n|rowspan=11|December 2005\n|rowspan=2|[[Bishop (comics)|Bishop]]\n|rowspan=2|Guns\n|long hair\n|rowspan=2|Bishop (1992) #2\n|rowspan=2|Lower torso\n|-\n|bald variant\n|-\n|[[Iron Fist (comics)|Iron Fist]]\n|rowspan=2|flame effects\n|Original costume\n|rowspan=2|Iron Fist (1975) #8\n|rowspan=2|leg, right\n|-\n|H'ylthri\n|red Iron Fist\n|-\n|[[Maestro (comics)|Maestro]]\n|crown\n|some packaged without the hose for connecting the left arm to the Apocalypse torso piece.\n|Captain Marvel (1999) #30\n|arm, left, arm tube\n|-\n|[[Sasquatch (comics)|Sasquatch]]\n|\n|\n|rowspan=2|Alpha Flight (1983) #10\n|rowspan=2|arm, right, arm tube\n|-\n|[[Snowbird (comics)|Snowbird]]\n|\n|Albino Sasquatch form (variant)\n|-\n|rowspan=2|Wolverine\n|rowspan=2|\n|[[Astonishing X-Men]] version\n|rowspan=2|Astonishing X-Men (2004) #6\n|rowspan=2|leg, left\n|-\n|unmasked Variant\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[X-23]]\n|rowspan=2|\n|black, straight hair\n|rowspan=2|Uncanny X-Men (1963) #451\n|rowspan=2|Head and upper torso\n|-\n|purple costume, wavy hair variant\n|-\n|rowspan=9|[[Onslaught (comics)|Onslaught]]\n|rowspan=9|May 2006\n|rowspan=2|[[Abomination (comics)|Abomination]]\n|rowspan=2|Diorama\n|regular\n|rowspan=2|Incredible Hulk (2000) #25\n|rowspan=2|arm, left\n|-\n|melted face variant\n|-\n|[[Blackheart]]\n|\n|\n|Wolverine; Ghost Rider; Punisher: Hearts of Darkness (1991) OGN\n|leg, left\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[Green Goblin]]\n|rowspan=2|Diorama\n|regular\n|rowspan=2|Amazing Spider-Man (1963) #122\n|rowspan=2|leg, right\n|-\n|unmasked variant\n|-\n|[[Lady Deathstrike]]\n|\n|\n|Wolverine (1988) #77\n|Upper torso\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[Loki (Marvel Comics)|Loki]]\n|rowspan=2|Diorama\n|regular\n|rowspan=2|Journey Into Mystery (1952) #116\n|rowspan=2|arm, right\n|-\n|''Crown of Lies'' variant\n|-\n|[[Pyro (Marvel Comics)|Pyro]]\n|\n|\n|Daredevil (1964) #355\n|Lower torso\n|-\n|rowspan=9|[[Mojo (comics)|Mojo]]\n|rowspan=9|August 2006\n|rowspan=2|[[Falcon (comics)|Falcon]] and Redwing\n|rowspan=2|\n|Classic\n|rowspan=2|Falcon (1983) #1\n|rowspan=2|Lower torso\n|-\n|modern costume variant\n|-\n|rowspan=2|Iron Man\n|rowspan=2|\n|first appearance grey armor version\n|rowspan=2|Tales Of Suspense (1959) #39 & 40\n|rowspan=2|metasoma\n|-\n|Gold variant\n|-\n|[[Longshot (Marvel Comics)|Longshot]]\n|\n|\n|X-Men (1991) #10\n|legs, right\n|-\n|[[Luke Cage]]\n|\n|\n|Hero For Hire (1972) #1\n|legs, left\n|-\n|[[Psylocke]]\n|\n|\n|Uncanny X-Men (1963) #258\n|Back torso\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[Baron Heinrich Zemo]]\n|row