cent\n|-\n|Iron Man\n|\n|[[Heroes Reborn (comics)|Heroes Reborn]] armor version\n|\n|Helmet and swords\n|-\n|[[Kang the Conqueror]]\n|\n|''Fantastic Four Classics'' repaint\n|\n|Upper torso\n|-\n|[[Spider-Man (Ben Reilly)]]\n|\n|\n|\n|Right arm\n|-\n|[[Vision (Marvel Comics)|Vision]]\n|\n|\n|\n|Right leg\n|-\n|[[War Machine]]\n|\n|Ultimate version\n|\n|Head\n|-\n|rowspan=8|[[Holocaust (Marvel Comics)|Holocaust]] (Nemesis)\n|rowspan=8|2009\n|[[Beast (comics)|Beast]]\n|\n|Astonishing X-Men version\n|\n|Right arm\n|-\n|[[Black Bolt]]\n|\n|\n|\n|Right leg\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[Daredevil (Marvel Comics character)|Daredevil]]\n|\n|First appearance yellow/brown\n|\n|rowspan=2|Lower torso\n|-\n|\n|Red variant\n|\n|-\n|[[Nova (Richard Rider)]]\n|\n|\n|\n|Left leg\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[Punisher]]\n|\n|Tim Bradstreet version\n|\n|rowspan=2|Left arm\n|-\n|\n|[[The Punisher (2005 video game)]] camo variant\n|-\n|[[Tigra]]\n|\n|\n|\n|Upper torso\n|}\n\n====Box Sets====\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!width=10%|'''Name'''\n!width=5%|'''Release'''\n!width=10%|'''Figure'''\n!width=30%|'''Accessories'''\n!width=33%|'''Description'''\n!width=10%|'''Pack-In'''\n|-\n|rowspan=4|[[Fantastic Four]]\n|rowspan=4|2005\n|[[Human Torch]]\n|Display Stand\n|Partial Flame-On\n|rowspan=4|''Fantastic Four Poster Book''\n|-\n|[[Invisible Woman]]\n|Display Stand\n|rowspan=2|Heroes Reborn Costume\n|-\n|[[Mr. Fantastic]]\n|Display Stand, Alternate elongated Hand and Mallet Hand\n|-\n|[[Thing (comics)|The Thing]]\n|Display Stand, Sunglasses, Hat and Removable Trenchcoat\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=2|Cable & Marvel Girl\n|rowspan=2|2007\n|[[Cable (comics)|Cable]]\n|2 guns\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[Jean Grey]]\n|\n|Green minidress\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=2|Cannonball & Domino\n|rowspan=2|2007\n|[[Cannonball (comics)|Cannonball]]\n|\n|Flight Jacket and Goggles (Late New Mutants) Costume<br />Exclusive\n|\n|-\n|[[Domino (comics)|Domino]]\n|2 Guns\n|Exclusive\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=2|Ultimate Spider-Man Versus Vulture\n|rowspan=2|2017\n|[[Ultimate Spider-Man (comic book)|Ultimate]] Spider-Man\n|Alternate hands\n|Ultimate Spider-Man Comic version<br />Repaint of Space Venom wave Ultimate Spider-Man\n|\n|-\n|[[Ultimate Spider-Man (comic book)|Ultimate]] [[Vulture (Marvel Comics)|Vulture]]\n|Alternate head from the ''[[Ultimate Spider-Man (TV series)|Ultimate Spider-Man]]'' animated series\n|Ultimate Spider-Man Comic version<br />Exclusive\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=2|Netflix\n|rowspan=2|2018\n|[[Luke Cage]]\n|\n|[[Luke Cage (TV series)]] version<br />Repaint of the SDCC exclusive figure\n|\n|-\n|[[Claire Temple (Marvel Cinematic Universe)|Claire Temple]]\n|Claw gauntlets, and latex glove hands\n|[[Iron Fist (TV series)]] version<br />Exclusive\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=2|Avengers: Infinity War\n|rowspan=2|2019\n|[[Corvus Glaive]]\n|Glaive\n|[[Avengers: Infinity War]] version<br />Exclusive\n|\n|-\n|[[Loki (Marvel Comics)|Loki]]\n|[[Cosmic Cube|Tesseract]]\n|[[Avengers: Infinity War]] version<br />Redeco of the Gladiator Hulk wave Loki\n|\n|}\n\n==Showdown==\n[[Marvel Legends Showdown]] is a collectible tabletop game in which the primary component is {{convert|4|in|mm|adj=on}} action figures and cards. It was a collaboration between [[Upper Deck Entertainment]] and Toy Biz. Originally known as Marvel Superhero Showdown.\n\n==Unleashed (2008)==\nFigures are {{convert|8|in|mm|adj=on}}. The figures were produced by Hasbro and feature multiple points of articulation.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:40%;\"\n|-\n!width=5%|'''Wave'''\n!width=15%|'''Figure'''\n!width=20%|'''Description'''\n|-\n|rowspan=2|1\n|Spider-Man\n|\n|-\n|Green Goblin\n|Marvel Knights costume\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2\n|Spider-Man\n|Symbiote costume\n|-\n|Doctor Octopus\n|\n|-\n|3\n|Iron Man\n|Anti-radiation armor\n|}\n\n==Icons==\nThe series is {{convert|12|in|mm|adj=on}}.\n\n===Toy Biz===\nFigures come with an \"Evolution of an Icon\" comic sized book including a history and statistics of the character as well as artwork.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" 