 line in all but name. The figures are more expensive and are therefore aimed at a more adult collector market.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n!width=5%|'''Release'''\n!width=15%|'''Figure'''\n!width=57%|'''Accessories'''\n!width=23%|'''Description'''\n|-\n|rowspan=3|2016\n|Iron Man\n|Alternate unmasked head, interchangeable hands and blast effects.\n|Model 37 Bleeding Edge armor<ref>http://marvel.wikia.com/wiki/Iron_Man_Armor_Model_37</ref>\n|-\n|Captain America\n|Shield, alternate unmasked head and helmet and interchangeable hands\n|[[Marvel NOW!]] version\n|-\n|Spider-Man\n|2 alternate heads and four interchangeable hands\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=5|2017\n|Deadpool and [[Headpool]]\n|2 alternate heads, 2 katanas, 2 guns, four alternate hands, 2 knives, a [[chimichanga]] and flight stand for Headpool\n|\n|-\n|Spider-Man\n|Alternate unmasked head and 4 interchangeable hands\n|Symbiote (Target exclusive)\n|-\n|Thor\n|Alternate helmeted head, 2interchangeable hands and 2 Mjolnirs\n|\n|-\n|Hulk\n|Alternate head and 2 interchangeable hands\n|\n|-\n|Daredevil\n|Alternate unmasked head and mask, six interchangeable hands and 2 batons\n|San Diego Comic Convention exclusive\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2018\n|Black Panther\n|Alternate unmasked head, Vibranium spear and 2 sets of interchangeable hands\n|[[Black Panther (film)]] version\n|-\n|Wolverine\n|2 alternate heads and a mask, 2 interchangeable hands and 2 interchangeable shoulder pads\n|\n|}\n\n==Prop Replicas==\nIn 2016, Hasbro announced a line of high end role play accessories. After the release of the first two items, a poll was held to determine future entries in the line.<ref>http://comicsalliance.com/hasbro-marvel-legends-role-play-vote/</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!width=10%|'''Release'''\n!width=30%|'''Item'''\n!width=60%|'''Description'''\n|-\n|\n|[[Iron Man]]'s helmet\n|removable faceplate<br />light-up eyes<br />sound effects\n|-\n|\n|[[Captain America's shield]]\n|adjustable straps\n|-\n|\n|[[Mjolnir (Marvel Comics)|Mjolnir]]\n|voice-activated light-up Odin symbol<br />sound effects<br />display stand\n|-\n|\n|[[Star-Lord]]'s helmet\n|[[Bluetooth]] speakers<br />light-up eyes\n|-\n|\n|[[Black Panther (comics)|Black Panther]]'s mask\n|light-up [[Vibranium]] effect<br />retractable lenses\n|-\n|\n|[[Infinity Gauntlet (weapon)|Infinity Gauntlet]]\n|light-up [[Infinity Stones]], sound effects, articulated fingers\n|-\n|\n|[[Ant-Man]]'s helmet\n|LEDs\n|-\n|\n|[[Infinity Gauntlet (weapon)|Stark Power Gauntlet]]\n|[[Avengers: Endgame]] version<br />light-up Infinity Stones\n|-\n|\n|[[War Machine]]'s helmet\n|[[Punisher (comics)|Punisher]] skull logo version<br />removable faceplate<br />light-up eyes<br />sound effects\n|}\n\n==Announced==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:5%;\"|'''Release'''\n! style=\"width:8%;\"|'''Wave'''\n! style=\"width:11%;\"|'''Figure'''\n! style=\"width:28%;\"|'''Accessories'''\n! style=\"width:40%;\"|'''Description'''\n! style=\"width:13%;\"|'''Build-A-Figure Piece'''\n|-\n|rowspan=7|2020\n|rowspan=7|[[Sugar Man]]\n|[[Alternative versions of Wolverine#Age of Apocalypse|Weapon X]] \n|Alternate left arm stub\n|rowspan=7|[[Age of Apocalypse]] version\n|Left leg\n|-\n|[[X-Man]]\n|\n|Top arms\n|-\n|[[Morph (Marvel Comics)|Morph]]\n|\n|Right leg\n|-\n|[[Wild Child (comics)|Wild Child]]\n|Chain\n|Torso\n|-\n|[[Sunfire (comics)|Sunfire]]\n|\n|Bottom arms\n|-\n|[[Dark Beast]]\n|Alternate hands\n|Hammer\n|-\n|[[Jean Grey]]\n|\n|Head\n|-\n\n|rowspan=5|2020\n|rowspan=5|[[Strong Guy]]\n|[[Deadpool]]\n|Twin katanas and rifle\n|Blue and yellow X-Men uniform version<br>Repaint of the Sasquatch wave Deadpool with different accessories\n|\n|-\n|[[Sunspot (comics)|Sunspot]]\n|2 energy effect pieces\n|rowspan=2|Rob Liefeld version\n|\n|-\n|[[Warpath (comics)|Warpath]]\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[Black Tom Cassidy]]\n|Shillelagh\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[Maverick (Marvel Comics)|Maverick]]\n|Gun\n|\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=7|2020\n|rowspan=7|[[Abomination (co