{"title_page": "Velvet (Adam Lambert album)", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Velvet\n| type         = studio\n| artist       = [[Adam Lambert]]\n| cover        = Adam Lambert - Velvet.png\n| alt          =\n| released     = {{Start date|2020|03|20|mf=y}}\n| recorded     =\n| studio       =\n| genre        = <!-- Please source any genres added to the article; all sourced in the \"Critical reception\" section. --> \n* [[Funk rock]]\n* [[disco]]\n* [[glam rock]]\n* [[Soul music|soul]]\n| length       = 44:00\n| label        = {{hlist|More Is More|[[Empire Distribution|Empire]]}}\n| producer     = {{hlist|[[Tommy English (producer)|Tommy English]]|[[Steve Booker (producer)|Steve Booker]]|Noise Club|[[Butch Walker]]|[[Fred Ball (producer)|Fred Ball]]}}\n| prev_title   = [[Velvet: Side A#Velvet: Side A (The Live Sessions)|Velvet: Side A (The Live Sessions)]]\n| prev_year    = 2019\n| next_title   =\n| next_year    =\n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = Adam Lambert studio album\n | type       = studio\n | prev_title = [[The Original High]]\n | prev_year  = 2015\n | title      = Velvet\n | year       = 2020\n | next_title = \n | next_year  = \n}}\n{{Singles\n| name         = Velvet\n| type         = studio\n| single1      = [[New Eyes (Adam Lambert song)|New Eyes]]\n| single1date  = May 15, 2019\n| single2      = Comin in Hot\n| single2date  = June 26, 2019\n| single3      = Superpower\n| single3date  = September 4, 2019\n| single4      = Roses\n| single4date  = February 4, 2020\n| single5      = Velvet\n| single5date  = March 20, 2020\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Velvet''''' (stylised in [[all caps]]) is the fourth studio album by American singer [[Adam Lambert]], released through More Is More and [[Empire Distribution]] on March 20, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/adam-lambert-announces-new-album-velvet-manchester-pride-performance-2605122|title=Adam Lambert announces new album 'Velvet' and Manchester Pride performance|work=[[NME]]|last=Daly|first=Rhian|date=February 4, 2020|accessdate=February 6, 2020}}</ref> It features the singles \"Feel Something\", \"[[New Eyes (Adam Lambert song)|New Eyes]]\", \"Comin' in Hot\", \"Superpower\", and \"Roses\" with [[Nile Rodgers]], as well as all the tracks featured on the ''[[Velvet: Side A]]'' EP, released in September 2019. Lambert is scheduled to promote the album with five appearances at [[the Venetian Las Vegas]] on April 18, 19, 22, 24 and 25 (currently postponed due to the [[2019-20 coronavirus pandemic|worldwide coronavirus outbreak]]) before embarking on a European tour from August to September 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ultimateclassicrock.com/adam-lambert-velvet-album/|title=Adam Lambert Announces New 'Velvet' Album|website=[[Ultimate Classic Rock]]|last=Lifton|first=Dave|date=February 4, 2020|accessdate=February 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\n\n==Background==\nLambert described the album as \"thirteen slinky numbers to catch a vibe to\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/adam-lambert-new-album-velvet-roses-947582/|title=Adam Lambert Announces New Album, Drops Funky Single 'Roses' Featuring Nile Rodgers|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|last=Martoccio|first=Angie|date=February 4, 2020|accessdate=February 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Critical reception ==\n{{Album ratings\n| MC = 84/100<ref>{{cite web |title=Velvet by Adam Lambert Reviews and Tracks |url=https://www.metacritic.com/music/velvet/adam-lambert |website=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=March 27, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"AllMusic\">{{cite web |last1=Collar |first1=Matt |title=''Velvet'' - Adam Lambert |url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/velvet-mw0003354659 |website=[[AllMusic]] |accessdate=March 22, 2020}}</ref>\n| rev2 = ''[[PopMatters]]''\n| rev2score = {{Rating|8|10}}<ref>{{cite web |last1=Davies |first1=Jeffrey |title=Adam Lambert Gets Nostalgic on 'Velvet' |url=https://www.popmatters.com/adam-lambert-velvet-review-2645572495.html?rebelltitem=2#rebelltitem2 |website=[[PopMatters]] |accessdate=March 27, 2020 |date=March 24, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n\nMike Wass of [[Idolator (website)|Idolator]] described ''Velvet'''s sound as a \"wild ride that incorporates everything from [[disco]] to [[glam rock]]\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Wass |first1=Mike |title=Adam Lambert Drops 'VELVET' LP, Unleashes Video For Epic Title Track |url=https://www.idolator.com/7908357/adam-lambert-drops-velvet-lp-unleashes-video-for-epic-title-track?view-all&adblock=1&chrome=1 |website=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]] |accessdate=March 22, 2020 |date=March 20, 2020}}</ref>, while Stephen Daw of ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' stated that the record was \"continuing in the same vein of late '60s [[funk rock]] that's fueled his latest releases\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Daw |first1=Stephen |title=On 'Velvet,' Adam Lambert Completes His Smooth-As-Silk Musical Journey |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/pride/9339526/adam-lambert-velvet-album-review |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=March 21, 2020 |date=March 20, 2020}}</ref> Writing for [[AllMusic]], Matt Collar called the album a \"new and delightfully retro direction\", as well as a \"dazzling, glitter-dipped exercise in '70s disco-era [[funk]], [[Rock music|rock]], and [[Soul music|soul]]\".<ref name=\"AllMusic\"/> A.D. Amorosi of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' praised the record, writing \"the 38-year-old out singer goes for something less glamorously amorously entertaining and more grimily soulful and sleekly funky than we\u2019re used to hearing from him\" and \"Adam Lambert has made \"Velvet\" a testament to finding his way, personally and professionally, in what is his most accomplished solo work to date\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Amorosi |first1=A.D. |title=Adam Lambert's 'Velvet': Album Review |url=https://variety.com/2020/music/reviews/adam-lambert-velvet-album-review-1203540452/ |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |accessdate=March 27, 2020 |date=March 20, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| extra_column = Producer\n| total_length = 44:00\n|headline = ''Velvet'' track listing\n| title1 = Velvet\n| writer1 = {{hlist|[[Adam Lambert]]|Ryan Daly|[[Busbee|Michael Busbee]]|[[Kinetics & One Love|Jeremy Dussolliet]]|[[Kinetics & One Love|Timothy Sommers]]}}\n| extra1 = [[Kinetics & One Love|Timothy Sommers]]\n| length1 = 2:58\n| title2 = Superpower\n| writer2 = {{hlist|Lambert|[[Ilsey Juber]]|[[Tommy English (producer)|Thomas Schlieter]]}}\n| extra2 = [[Tommy English (producer)|Tommy English]]\n| length2 = 3:10\n| title3 = Stranger You Are\n| writer3 = {{hlist|Lambert|Kes Kross|[[Steve Booker (producer)|Steve Booker]]}}\n| extra3 = S<!-- Do not shorten producers' names until they've at least been named in full once in the producer column -->teve Booker\n| length3 = 2:52\n| title4 = Loverboy\n| writer4 = {{hlist|Lambert|[[Gabe Simon|Gabriel Simon]]|Schlieter|[[Angelo Petraglia]]}}\n| extra4 = English\n| length4 = 3:20\n| title5 = Roses\n| note5 = with [[Nile Rodgers]]\n| writer5 = {{hlist|Lambert|Kross|[[Fred Ball (producer)|Frederik Ball]]}}\n| extra5 = [[Fred Ball (producer)|Fred Ball]]\n| length5 = 3:49\n| title6 = Closer to You\n| writer6 = {{hlist|Lambert|Asia Whiteacre|Robert McCurdy|Christopher Petrosino}}\n| extra6 = NoiseClub\n| length6 = 4:19\n| title7 = Overglow\n| writer7 = {{hlist|Lambert|[[Amy Kuney]]|[[Butch Walker]]|[[MNEK|Uzoechi Emenike]]}}\n| extra7 = Butch Walker\n| length7 = 3:32\n| title8 = Comin in Hot\n| writer8 = {{hlist|Lambert|Katie Pearlman|Michelle Buzz|[[The Monarch (production team)|Andre Davidson]]|[[The Monarch (production team)|Sean Davidson]]}}\n| extra8 = [[The Monarch (production team)|The Monarch]]\n| length8 = 2:48\n| title9 = On the Moon\n| writer9 = {{hlist|Lambert|[[Sam Sparro|Samuel Falson]]|[[Britt Burton|Brittany Burton]]|Jorgen Odegard|[[Xela (musician)|Alexander Go]]}}\n| extra9 = Odegard\n| length