{"title_page": "John Oldfield (footballer)", "text_new": "{{For|the English footballer named John Edward Oldfield|Ted Oldfield}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2017}}\n{{Use British English|date=December 2017}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = John Oldfield\n| fullname = John Stephen Oldfield\n| birth_date = {{birth date|1943|8|19|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Lindrick]], England\n| death_date = {{death date and age|2002|10||1943|8|19|df=y}}\n| death_place = Leeds, England\n| position = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]]\n|  years1 =   1963\u20131969 \n| years2 =  1969\u20131971 \n| years3 =  1971 \n| years4 =  1971\u20131973\n|  clubs1 =   [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]]  \n| clubs2 =   [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]]  \n| clubs3 =   \u2192 [[Crewe Alexandra F.C.|Crewe Alexandra]] (loan)  \n| clubs4 =   [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]]\n| caps1 =    152   \n| caps2 =    19   \n| caps3 =     5   \n| caps4 =    31  \n| goals1 =  0  \n| goals2 =  0  \n| goals3 =  0  \n| goals4 =  0 \n}}\n'''John Stephen Oldfield''' (born 19 August 1943) is a former professional [[association football|footballer]], who played for [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]], [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]], [[Crewe Alexandra F.C.|Crewe Alexandra]] and [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]].\n\nJohn Oldfield was a keeper who set a record by saving penalties in successive games against Arsenal and Liverpool more than 40 years ago.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.wolvesheroes.com/2013/09/03/fondly-remembered-john-oldfield/|title=Wolves Heroes \u00bb Blog Archive \u00bb Fondly Remembered: John Oldfield|access-date=2016-10-14}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n*{{cite book|title=99 Years and Counting: Stats and Stories|author=Ian Thomas, Owen Thomas, Alan Hodgson, John Ward|year=2007|publisher=Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|ISBN=095572810X}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Oldfield, John}}\n[[Category:1943 births]]\n[[Category:2002 deaths]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football goalkeepers]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:Huddersfield Town A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Crewe Alexandra F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Bradford City A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing]]\n\n\n{{Ireland-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{For|the English footballer named John Edward Oldfield|Ted Oldfield}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2017}}\n{{Use British English|date=December 2017}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = John Oldfield\n| fullname = John Stephen Oldfield\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1943|8|19|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Lindrick]], [[UK]]\n| death_date = October 2002\n| death_place = Leeds, UK\n| position = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]]\n|  years1 =   1963\u20131969 \n| years2 =  1969\u20131971 \n| years3 =  1971 \n| years4 =  1971\u20131973\n|  clubs1 =   [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]]  \n| clubs2 =   [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]]  \n| clubs3 =   \u2192 [[Crewe Alexandra F.C.|Crewe Alexandra]] (loan)  \n| clubs4 =   [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]]\n| caps1 =    152   \n| caps2 =    19   \n| caps3 =     5   \n| caps4 =    31  \n| goals1 =  0  \n| goals2 =  0  \n| goals3 =  0  \n| goals4 =  0 \n}}\n'''John Stephen Oldfield''' (born 19 August 1943 in Lindrick, [[United Kingdom]]) is a former [[professional]] [[association football|footballer]], who played for [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]], [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]], [[Crewe Alexandra F.C.|Crewe Alexandra]] and [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]].\n\nJohn Oldfield was a keeper who set a record by saving penalties in successive games against Arsenal and Liverpool more than 40 years ago.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.wolvesheroes.com/2013/09/03/fondly-remembered-john-oldfield/|title=Wolves Heroes \